title: HK-2
characteristics_ch1.1: cell type: Human renal epithelial cells
extract_protocol_ch1: RNA of cells and exosomes was isolated using Trizol Plus RNA purification kit (Life Technologies, 12183555) according to manufacturer's protocol. The quality of the total RNA was assessed by Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer using an RNA 6000 Pico Kit (Agilent Technologies). After verifying the quality of RNA, we proceeded to the second part of the protocol of small RNA enrichment from total RNA by increasing ethanol content of the sample and isolation over glass-fiber filter and elution. Later, quality of the small RNA samples was analyzed by Agilent 2100 Bioanalyzer using a Small RNA kit (Agilent Technologies). RNA total concentration was measured by Nanodrop, and miRNA concentration was measured with the Quant-iT RiboGreen Kit (Thermo-Scientific).
extract_protocol_ch1.1: RNA libraries were prepared for sequencing using standard Illumina protocols.
data_processing.1: Sequenced reads were trimmed for adaptor sequence, and masked for low-complexity or low-quality sequence, then got the clean reads.
data_processing.2: Clean reads was classified and annotated to obtain the component and expression information of various sRNA in samples, the miRNA database is from miRBase version 21.
data_processing.3: nCRNA sequences other than miRNA sequences in clean data were removed, and the remaining sequences were compared with all mature miRNA sequences of the species in the miRBase database, the number of reads per million (RPM) clean reads that were aligned to a specific miRNA was calculated.
data_processing.5: Supplementary_files_format_and_content: *.miR.expre.txt: Tab-delimited text files include RPM values for each sample.
